                    "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                    "paragraphTitle": "Articles",
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "We use the indefinite article (a/an):",
                        "when we talk about something for the first time",
                        "when it’s not clear or important which one of a group is being talked about"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "We use the definite article (the):",
                        "when there’s only one of something",
                        "when it’s clear which thing we’re talking about (usually because we’ve mentioned it before)",
                        "with superlatives",
                        "with rivers, some mountains, oceans, seas, plural country names, groups of islands and deserts"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "We use the zero article (-):",
                        "to talk about things in general",
                        "with most towns, cities, countries, continents, states, lakes and mountains"
                    ]
                }
            ],
